President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver a national message on Sunday afternoon during the virtual commemoration of Human Rights Day. Remembering Sharpeville-Langa Day:  President @CyrilRamaphosa to deliver national message on Human Rights Day https://t.co/7Z9P9aVHf0 — Presidency | South Africa  (@PresidencyZA) March 20, 2021  The Human Rights Month is this year is celebrated under the theme “The Year of Charlotte Maxeke: Promoting Human Rights in the Age of COVID-19”. The theme pays tribute to the 150th anniversary of the birth of liberation struggle veteran and human rights campaigner, Charlotte Maxeke.